                                <date>1958</date>. С. <biblScope unit="page">??–??</biblScope>.</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><encodingDesc><tagsDecl>&amp;renditions;</tagsDecl></encodingDesc></teiHeader><text><body><entry xml:id="entry_æna" xml:lang="os"><form type="lemma"><orth>æna</orth></form><sense><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>мама</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>mama</q></tr></sense><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>матушка</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>mother</q></tr></sense><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>бабушка</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>granny</q></tr></sense><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">детское и почтительно-ласковое название для матери, бабки: </note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en">childish or honorific/diminutive name for mother, grandmother: </note></sense><exampleGrp><example xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg><lang/></usg><quote>ox, æna, ci kænon!</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>о, мать, что мне делать!</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>oh mother, what should I do!</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Iræf"/><biblScope>22</biblScope></bibl></example><example><quote>æna xæbīzǵyn k˳y skodta...</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>когда матушка приготовила пирог с сыром...</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>when mother made a cheese pie...</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_ОТ"/><biblScope>96</biblScope></bibl></example><example><quote>ūs уn zaǧta; ænajy nom myl k˳у næ sæværdtais, wæd dæ axordtain</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>женщина ему сказала: если бы ты не назвал меня %sæna%s, я бы тебя съела</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>the woman told him: if you had not called me %sæna%s, I would have eaten you</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Munk."/><biblScope>82</biblScope></bibl></example></exampleGrp><exampleGrp><example xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg><lang/></usg><quote>ox, æna, ci kænon!</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>о, мать, что мне делать!</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>oh mother, what should I do!</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Iræf"/><biblScope>22</biblScope></bibl></example><example><quote>æna xæbīzǵyn k˳y skodta...</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>когда матушка приготовила пирог с сыром...</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>when mother made a cheese pie...</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_ОТ"/><biblScope>96</biblScope></bibl></example><example><quote>ūs уn zaǧta; ænajy nom myl k˳у næ sæværdtais, wæd dæ axordtain</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>женщина ему сказала: если бы ты не назвал меня %sæna%s, я бы тебя съела</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>the woman told him: if you had not called me %sæna%s, I would have eaten you</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Munk."/><biblScope>82</biblScope></bibl></example></exampleGrp><etym xml:lang="ru">Ср. <mentioned xml:lang="trk"><lang/> <w>ana</w> <gloss><q>мать</q></gloss></mentioned>. Распространено в кавказских языках: <mentioned xml:lang="ab"><lang/> <w>an</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="x-crc"><lang/> <w>anne</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="kbd"><lang/> <w>hane</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ce"><lang/> <w>na</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="inh"><lang/> <w>na</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="dar"><lang/> <w>ana</w> <gloss><q>мать</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="dar"><w/> <gloss><q>бабушка</q></gloss></mentioned>, . Ср. также <mentioned xml:lang="hit"><lang/> <w>anna</w> <gloss><q>мать</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="la"><lang/> <w>anna</w> <gloss><q>кормилица</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><lang/> <w>ἀννίς</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="goh"><lang/> <w>ana</w> <gloss><q>бабушка</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="prg"><lang/> <w>ane</w> <gloss><q>старая мать</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ps"><lang/> <w>ana</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="hu"><lang/> <w>anja</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="kca"><lang/> <w>ana</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="udm"><lang/> <w>anaj</w> <gloss><q>мать</q></gloss></mentioned> и др. „Детское“ слово. Симметричный термин для ‘отца’ — <ref type="xr" target="#entry_æda"/> q. v. См. также <ref type="xr" target="#entry_nana"/>, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_dada"/>.</etym><etym xml:lang="en">Compare with <mentioned xml:lang="trk"><lang/> <w>ana</w> <gloss><q>mother</q></gloss></mentioned>. Widespread in Caucasian languages: <mentioned xml:lang="ab"><lang/> <w>an</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="x-crc"><lang/> <w>anne</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="kbd"><lang/> <w>hane</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ce"><lang/> <w>na</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="inh"><lang/> <w>na</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="dar"><lang/> <w>ana</w> <gloss><q>mother</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="dar"><w/> <gloss><q>grandmother</q></gloss></mentioned>, . Consider also <mentioned xml:lang="hit"><lang/> <w>anna</w> <gloss><q>mother</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="la"><lang/> <w>anna</w> <gloss><q>foster-mother</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><lang/> <w>ἀννίς</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="goh"><lang/> <w>ana</w> <gloss><q>grandmother</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="prg"><lang/> <w>ane</w> <gloss><q>old mother</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ps"><lang/> <w>ana</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="hu"><lang/> <w>anja</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="kca"><lang/> <w>ana</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="udm"><lang/> <w>anaj</w> <gloss><q>mother</q></gloss></mentioned> etc. “Children's” language word. Symmetrical term for ‘father’ is <ref type="xr" target="#entry_æda"/> q. v. See also <ref type="xr" target="#entry_nana"/>, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_dada"/>.</etym></entry></body></text></TEI>